<br>
I feel that allowing such a psychotic rate of progression will be harmful...even though I'm not playing my main char much now like I haven't been for several months, I still feel my fun in the game inhibited by this. <p>Sauron: Well, you get enough of em together and they are actually able to take down a Ranger. <br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=42500"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://sageofrain.com/aekasig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/bdrinal28133.showUserPublicProfile?gid=panamah>Panamah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><HR><font color=#FF0000>Drinal Ally</font><HR></span><br>  Posts: 533<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/22/03 6:13:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2012.topic&index=51>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://nmcs.com/kingscourt/images/panamah_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /flame raid disruptions</span><hr size=1> The raid stuff in EQ is to manage raids.  Before it ever existed how large was a raid &quot;supposed&quot; to be?  They decided a reasonable maximum raid size for their tool was 72 probably because they felt most of their encounters could be done by 72 or less.  I don't think I've ever seen a rule that says you can't have a raid with more than 72.  In fact, I think a few guilds have been combining up to do Aerin'Dar and I know they're talking more than 72 people along to kill.<br>
<br>
I remember when in the old days we'd take a zillion groups down to the Hole to do epic stuff.  It got to the point where we could do it with 2-3 people botting 6 character.  Does that mean that Hole raids should only have 6 characters?  <br>
<br>
While 200 was plainly too big because of the lag and stuff, I don't think EQ encounters for the most part were necessarily designed with any particular number in mind.  Some of them enforce a number and those clearly are designed that way.  <br>
<br>
But something that an uber guild can do with 20 is going to take 40 or 60 of someone else.  That doesn't mean that the people it takes 60 of are talentless, no-goods, it means they don't have the levels or equipment or maybe they're just erring on the side of caution because it's their first time.<br>
<br>
Psychotic rate of progression?  I have been stuck in Tier 2 planes since November 1st.  That means I've spent night after night after night in PoV for a lot of months now.  I now get to access another 2 zones after almost 4 months of owning PoP.  Not exactly blowing through PoP content am I? <br>
<br>
The important thing is I, and others, feel like we're progressing again and it's really increased my enjoyment of EQ.  I was so close to quitting that I had cancelled all my accounts and was waiting for them to expire.  If helping people, and myself, get some additional enjoyment out of this game is so disturbing to some people I really have to wonder what kind of Grinches people are. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/bdrinal28133.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kaladornus>kaladornus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><HR><font color=#FF0000>Drinal Ally</font><HR></span><br>  Posts: 589<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/22/03 10:57:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2012.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /flame raid disruptions</span><hr size=1> The fact that getting through the trials and being able to be Level 65 with 100 AA's in two to three months scares me. <br>
<br>
5 hours a day exp is easily 2 Yellows in inner caves in PoV...20-25 days to finish 61-65. 2 AA's a night is easy in 5 hours at level 65...another 50 days or so. <br>
<br>
Average this out with weekends or whatever and your hardcore exp'rs can do it with room to spare. <br>
<br>
Regular exp'rs can get to 65 in two months easy and have some AA to show for it...<br>
<br>
The fact that there are all these pent-up level 65's that still need to kill pre-PoP content for equipment upgrades scares me.<br>
<br>
The fact that level 65 makes all the old fights much more gimpy scares me.<br>
<br>
The fact that AA and level DPS increases can allow you to skip sleeper's Tomb scares me.<br>
<br>
The fact that they decided to basically make old world challenge much easier/trivial and didn't provide a format or entire world in PoP at LEAST as big as the previous 3 expansions scares me.<br>
<br>
So what you have now is Level 65 in a couple months, an increased number of people/guilds able to do Ssra, NToV, etc...and a huge blockage of getting people a chance to try the stuff in PoP they are now appropriately levelled for.<br>
<br>
Yikes.<br>
<br>
That scares me. Mega-raids at least get people a little more spread out. If UF or GotK or UC or Avatar or Unrivaled or DM whoever (they are all AoW-caliber now - P.S. if they havent killed yet they can or will extremely soon) gets a chance to get their guild flagged through this and up to tactics or Elemental planes or whatever....<br>
<br>
Then you finally start to see some of the comparable loot that you saw in the incredibly easier Ssra mobs or even VT (assuming you can kill emp some day and collect shards, etc...)<br>
<br>
So having WL/CT/TK in Air and Fire and Water and Earth and GotK/UF/DM/Ava/Unrivaled in HoHB or BoT or PoT or wherever helps alleviate some of this pressure from the issue I am talking about.<br>
<br>
Even if Mega-raids end up taking out RZ, there is too much going on in the elemental planes for TK/WL/CT/CiH to be covering it all at once. Some content would get left untouched in any event due to the large scale raids you need to farm and progress here.<br>
<br>
So, I think there is room here for everyone. But you have to get some of the up and comers into zones where they won't look at AoW or KT or Yeli or NToV or whoever anymore and say, ok we HAVE to do that.<br>
<br>
Because guess what? White Wind and Divine Intervention and Drinal Alliance and all the other heretofore unnoticed guilds will be pushing up against those same mobs because as soon as you get one group through those trials, if they are the right people, motivated etc...then you can get a whole guild through.<br>
<br>
Once that happens, you could have 40 members at level 65 in two or three months easy.<br>
<br>
I agree that the rate of advancement is scary here. You have to hope that elemental armor, etc...<br>
<br>
Makes CiH and CT and WL and TK want to LIVE in the elemental planes. (as in, have a major boss pop each day after the expansion, take 5 or 6 hours to complete AND blow away your conception of loot - which isn't the way it is currently set up <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
You have to hope the next tier down guilds either get access to Elemental planes AND there is room to share to get gear OR that they can find NToV/Ssra equivalency in Tier 3. Only then....<br>
<br>
The rest of the guilds then get to diivy up the pie that currently belongs to UC/DM/UNR/AVA/UF/GOTK.<br>
<br>
The big problem, however, is that if you don't keep people occupied for 7 straight days a week in the higher tier planes then you will still have 18 people from CiH or WL or CT or TK come down and kill Cazic-thule for instance for a choker or a brain.<br>
<br>
But you are correct. Getting a ringer group to pull people through to PoV and PoS is not tough. Levelling in PoV/PoS with the appropriate supporting cast is not tough. <br>
<br>
A supporting cast you will always have because getting AA's in PoV/PoS is also very easy.<br>
<br>
What this means is that if you have the werewithal to level up to 56+ (which is now very easy given new exp spots, twink items, etc) and a few friends, you basically have your meal ticket to level 65.<br>
<br>
The power of 12-18 level 65's on old world content is frightening.<br>
<br>
I say get as many of these level 65's access to these zones as fast as possible. If Verant did its job right, the less powerful guilds will never see them again in Dragon Necropolis or Running across Western Wastes. <br>
<br>
But having them hang around waiting for Rumblecrush to pop or with 200 people in Kael on patch day?<br>
<br>
No thank you.<br>
<br>
Jakle<br>
<br>
P.S. The vision was obliterated a long time ago. Mob mentality and the entree of new, easier to level games requiring less dedication and skill (DAoC) obviously spooked Sony/reduced Player counts. I.E. you don't get any growth Serverwide messages anymore.<br>
<br>
I think flagging people will help the overall health of the server/player relations. I might be wrong.<br>
